Severe storms wreaked havoc in Southern California, leaving thousands without power and triggering mudslides and floods.
Tragedy struck when a hillside collapsed in Los Angeles, burying a man in a tent.
Rescuers worked tirelessly to free people trapped in their homes and vehicles.
The region faced a transportation crisis as major roads and rail lines were closed due to weather-related incidents.
Despite the devastation, there were miraculous stories of survival, like a hiker rescued after being trapped for days.
The community rallied together in the face of nature's fury, highlighting the resilience of Californians.
